Plot.
It's 1975, we witness the birth of the partnership of undercover cops
Starsky and Hutch. One is uptight and by-the-book, the butt of hazing
by other officers; he runs through a dozen partners in two years. The
other steals from bookies and hangs out with low-lifes. Bad-guy Reese
Feldman is importing an odorless, tasteless cocaine that fools drug
sniffing dogs. One of his murder victims washes up on shore about the
time Hutch's informants tell him a big cocaine deal is going down. But
our fearless duo moves too quickly, and they are suspended from the
force; the partnership founders amid bad feeling. Can they patch it up
don disguises, and ferret out where the murderer hid the coke?
